================ SYNTHESIS ================
The critics converge on one genuinely reachable catastrophe and two supporting weaknesses. The primary issue is that runMonthlyInterest sets only principal:true, but releasePayment's conjunctive guard requires all three flags to suppress â€” so every monthly run wires out the full principal as a live outbound wire. The confirmation guard offers no protection (no-op return, unchecked, no amount shown), and the interest amount is never actually computed. I merged the many duplicate reports of each and ranked by what actually happens on an ordinary run.

